children.subject: Can we also be notified when the system is fixed?
When you add classes to your shopping cart, there is an option to check whether or not you want to be added to the waitlist if the class is full.
How do we add a class onto the waitlist?

history.content:
I believe you will be able to enroll in upper div cs classes by later this morning (by 10:30am or so). Please try again then and if it's still not fixed again this afternoon and finally tomorrow morning.  I'm fairly certain you should be able to enroll by then but if not please reach out again Wednesday afternoon.

Unfortunately, we don't have the capacity to keep parallel lists to make up for campus system failures.

I believe you will be able to enroll in upper div cs classes by later this morning (by 10:30am or so). Please try again then and if it's still not fixed again this afternoon and finally tomorrow morning.  I'm fairly certain you should be able to enroll by then but if not please reach out again Wednesday afternoon.

I am a 2nd semester junior, who will be a senior in F16. I am already a senior in units just like many people.

Just like everyone else, I am currently unable to enroll in any upper div CS classes.

Because everyone has been putting themselves on the waitlist instead, the waitlist is already full for the class I really want to take. I can't even put myself on the waitlist.

Until the system is fixed, can we somehow leave a record of what class we intend to enroll in for phase 1? Otherwise, I feel like there is no benefit at all for having an earlier phase 1 appointment date.
